headlines.description: — Alex Sarr made the go-ahead basket with 53 seconds left, followed with a blocked shot and finished with 19 points to lead the Washington Wizards to a 129-125 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sarr scores 19 points, makes big plays on both ends late as Wizards beat Pistons 129-125

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 24 points, 12 rebounds and nine assists, and the Milwaukee Bucks snapped a three-game skid with a 126-106 victory over the short-handed Los Angeles Lakers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks withstand Doncic's 45-point effort and end 3-game skid with 126-106 victory over Lakers

headlines.description: — Coby White scored 31 points, and the Chicago Bulls beat the Brooklyn Nets 116-110 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coby White scores 31 points as Bulls rally to beat Nets 116-110

events.name: Orlando Magic at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero had 34 points, 11 rebounds and four steals, and the Orlando Magic beat the New Orleans Pelicans 113-93 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero scores 34 points and Magic build a 30-point halftime lead in a 113-93 rout of the Pelicans

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry became the first player in NBA history with 4,000 career 3-pointers, Draymond Green scored 23 points and the Golden State Warriors beat the Sacramento Kings 130-104 on Thursday night for their sixth straight victory and 11th of 12.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry reaches 4,000 career 3-pointers, Warriors hold off Kings for 6th straight win
